ACID properties ensure the reliability of database transactions by maintaining essential guarantees.
Atomicity ensures that all operations within a transaction either succeed together or fail.
Consistency guarantees that the database remains valid before and after a transaction adhering.
Isolation ensures that concurrent transactions do not interfere with each other.
Durability guarantees that once a transaction is committed its effects are permanently saved in the database.

